1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:56,010
Straight Ahead!

3
00:01:56,430 --> 00:01:58,470
Whoa! Look behind him!

4
00:01:58,970 --> 00:02:00,560
A rainbow! There's a rainbow!

5
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:05,270
Even the way he cries is big!

6
00:02:05,650 --> 00:02:07,360
It's practically a waterfall!

7
00:02:07,980 --> 00:02:10,820
I understand how you feel,
Master Brogy!

8
00:02:29,710 --> 00:02:32,170
Dorry! How are you...?

9
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:36,590
It seems I blacked out.

10
00:02:39,390 --> 00:02:41,430
Mr. 0?

11
00:02:42,270 --> 00:02:47,400
Wasn't "Mr. 0" the name
of the enemy boss Vivi mentioned?

12
00:02:48,230 --> 00:02:52,360
Which means the guy I'm talking to
on this transponder snail...

13
00:02:58,240 --> 00:03:00,450
is one of the Seven Warlords of the Sea?!

14
00:03:00,450 --> 00:03:04,370
I issued your orders several days ago.

15
00:03:04,370 --> 00:03:06,290
What in the world is going on?

16
00:03:06,290 --> 00:03:08,380
It says "Mr. 3."

17
00:03:08,380 --> 00:03:11,250
So he's the owner
of this transponder snail?

18
00:03:12,550 --> 00:03:15,380
It's all coming together now.

19
00:03:15,380 --> 00:03:17,010
This is an enemy hideout,

20
00:03:17,010 --> 00:03:22,060
and a guy named Mr. 3
came to the island to take Vivi's life.

21
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:24,770
Damn...

22
00:03:24,770 --> 00:03:27,690
I wasted all this time hunting!

23
00:03:27,690 --> 00:03:29,810
I hope everyone's okay!

24
00:03:31,270 --> 00:03:33,480
Why the silent treatment?

25
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:36,450
I asked you a question.

26
00:03:36,450 --> 00:03:40,030
Have you eliminated Princess Vivi
and the Straw Hats?!

27
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:43,160
Yeah, mission accomplished!

28
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:47,750
I got rid of everyone
who knew your secret.

29
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:50,000
This means we can call off the dogs.

30
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,130
I see. Well done.

31
00:03:53,130 --> 00:03:56,260
As we speak, the Unluckies
are headed your way

32
00:03:56,260 --> 00:04:00,090
to verify the mission's accomplishment
and to deliver a certain package.

33
00:04:00,550 --> 00:04:02,930
Unluckies? Package?

34
00:04:02,930 --> 00:04:06,980
An eternal pose that points
to the Kingdom of Alabasta.

35
00:04:08,100 --> 00:04:13,730
You and Miss Golden Week
will need to make your way there.

36
00:04:13,730 --> 00:04:15,110
The time has come.

37
00:04:15,110 --> 00:04:19,610
We will commence our
most critical operation to date.

38
00:04:19,610 --> 00:04:23,030
Once in Alabasta,
await further orders.

39
00:04:26,830 --> 00:04:28,460
Who the hell are these guys?!

40
00:04:32,590 --> 00:04:34,050
Hey. What's the problem?

41
00:04:34,420 --> 00:04:36,510
Oh, no worries. It's noth–

42
00:04:39,010 --> 00:04:40,130
What the hell?!

43
00:04:56,190 --> 00:04:57,740
You wanna kill me?!

44
00:04:57,740 --> 00:05:00,780
Bring it on, you damn monkey!

45
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,660
How about you...

46
00:05:12,380 --> 00:05:14,170
give it a rest,

47
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:16,710
you oversized chicken!

48
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:24,550
What was that?! What happened?!

49
00:05:24,550 --> 00:05:28,520
Oh, i-it's nothing. Nothing at all.

50
00:05:29,140 --> 00:05:31,480
That damn Straw Hat was still alive.

51
00:05:31,810 --> 00:05:36,360
It's okay, though. I finished him off.
No need to worry.

52
00:05:37,530 --> 00:05:39,740
Still alive?

53
00:05:40,490 --> 00:05:43,910
You told me "mission accomplished."

54
00:05:43,910 --> 00:05:45,700
Didn't you?

55
00:05:47,330 --> 00:05:49,120
Well, yes.

56
00:05:49,620 --> 00:05:51,830
I thought it was, y'know?

57
00:05:52,540 --> 00:05:56,040
But that bastard was a lot
tougher than you'd imagine.

58
00:05:56,920 --> 00:06:02,340
In other words, what you
gave me was a false report.

59
00:06:02,970 --> 00:06:07,720
Um, well... I suppose
that's what it sounds like.

60
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:10,850
But he won't be
coming back from this one.

61
00:06:10,850 --> 00:06:13,560
So, no need to send
anyone else. Capisce?

62
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,730
Enough.

63
00:06:15,730 --> 00:06:20,530
You're to head straight
to Alabasta immediately!

64
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:27,120
It must've been...
due to the weapons.

65
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:29,620
The weapons?! Of course!

66
00:06:30,410 --> 00:06:33,330
Not even weapons forged in Elbaph

67
00:06:33,330 --> 00:06:37,630
could withstand a century-long
duel between giants!

68
00:06:39,130 --> 00:06:40,880
Of all the crazy luck...

69
00:06:41,510 --> 00:06:42,800
What a miracle!

70
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:48,760
Hey, Brogy! Quit squeezing!
You'll open my wounds!

71
00:06:49,260 --> 00:06:52,430
I'm so glad you're alive, old friend!

72
00:06:57,610 --> 00:07:00,520
What miracle?
This was bound to happen.

73
00:07:00,980 --> 00:07:05,700
After 100 years of clashing and clanging,
it's crazier that those weapons are still intact.

74
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:07,200
Not to mention their owners.

75
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:10,580
This is truly a glorious day!

76
00:07:10,580 --> 00:07:12,660
I give thanks to the gods of Elbaph!

77
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,500
Oh, Brogy?

78
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:20,590
So cutting me down and taking me out
was a joyous occasion?

79
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:24,220
You numbskull!
You have the wrong idea!

80
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:27,680
Ouch! Watch out for my wounds!

81
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,900
You want some more?!

82
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:42,530
Yeah! I'll drop you again!

83
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:48,410
Cool! Cool! Cool! Cool!

84
00:07:49,410 --> 00:07:51,870
Why are you guys at it again?!

85
00:07:52,490 --> 00:07:56,710
From here on out,
practice radio silence.

86
00:07:56,710 --> 00:07:59,830
It'll keep the Marines
from catching on to us.

87
00:08:00,380 --> 00:08:05,170
All further orders will be sent
in writing, as per usual.

88
00:08:05,170 --> 00:08:08,800
That is all. Good luck, Mr. 3.

89
00:08:16,310 --> 00:08:18,310
Miss All-Sunday.

90
00:08:20,190 --> 00:08:20,980
Yes?

91
00:08:20,980 --> 00:08:24,480
Have Mr. 2 head to Little Garden.

92
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:31,740
Mr. 3 will meet his demise
en route to Alabasta from Little Garden.

93
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:36,700
How cold-blooded of you,
Sir "Mr. 0" Crocodile.

94
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:39,250
We have enough manpower as it is.

95
00:08:39,750 --> 00:08:42,330
Are you questioning my decision?

96
00:08:42,330 --> 00:08:44,550
No, I'll do as you wish.

97
00:08:44,550 --> 00:08:46,460
I'll make arrangements at once.

98
00:08:50,050 --> 00:08:51,680
Well, he hung up.

99
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:52,760
Let's see...

100
00:08:53,260 --> 00:08:56,140
Just who were these guys?

101
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:03,860
What's this?

102
00:09:03,900 --> 00:09:09,700
At Sea (The Grand Line)

103
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:07,610
Captain Smoker! Captain Smoker!

104
00:09:07,610 --> 00:09:09,700
We intercepted an intriguing transmission.

105
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:11,200
What?

106
00:09:14,490 --> 00:09:17,040
What an incredible full temper!

107
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:18,870
The fine grade sword, Kashu!

108
00:09:19,620 --> 00:09:21,670
Tashigi! Hey, Tashigi!

109
00:09:21,670 --> 00:09:26,880
Only on the Grand Line can you
find a named blade so readily!

110
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:28,260
Tashigi! Hey!

111
00:09:28,260 --> 00:09:30,300
Are you deaf, you sword freak?!

112
00:09:30,300 --> 00:09:31,260
Y-Yes, sir!

113
00:09:31,260 --> 00:09:33,220
What is it, Captain Smoker?!
The coffee is–

114
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:42,140
Just get over here and listen to this!

115
00:09:43,690 --> 00:09:47,610
Listen close. We just picked up
this conversation between two men.

116
00:09:47,610 --> 00:09:49,570
Are you ready, Chief?
Let's play it back.

117
00:09:49,570 --> 00:09:51,780
Y-Yes. If you would.

118
00:09:53,570 --> 00:09:54,990
...'s me. Mr. 0.

119
00:09:55,450 --> 00:09:57,950
Princess Vivi and the Straw Ha...

120
00:09:58,790 --> 00:10:01,000
Straw Ha...? The Straw Hat Pirates!

121
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:03,120
Yeah, mission accomplished!

122
00:10:04,670 --> 00:10:08,420
...further orders will...
in writing, as per usual.

123
00:10:05,460 --> 00:10:10,130
Black Wiretapper Snail

124
00:10:08,420 --> 00:10:10,130
That is all. Good luck...

125
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:14,300
The rest is indecipherable.

126
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:20,100
The signal was faint, but we made out
four keywords in this conversation:

127
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:26,730
Princess Vivi; Straw Hat;
written orders; and Mr. 0.

128
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:30,150
Mr. 0? Could that be a code name?!

129
00:10:30,150 --> 00:10:32,610
If so, could he be connected to that

130
00:10:32,610 --> 00:10:35,200
suspicious swordsman
we caught back in Renaisse?

131
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:43,160
Mr. 11
Frontier Agent, Baroque Works

132
00:10:36,030 --> 00:10:38,370
Connected to him... Mr. 11?

133
00:10:38,370 --> 00:10:39,910
Yeah, seems like it.

134
00:10:39,910 --> 00:10:43,250
A criminal organization
with numerical code names

135
00:10:43,250 --> 00:10:45,830
that sends written orders
to carry out missions.

136
00:10:45,830 --> 00:10:47,500
Sound about right?

137
00:10:48,090 --> 00:10:51,210
Mr. 0? Criminal organization? Beats me.

138
00:10:51,210 --> 00:10:52,670
I've no time for riddles.

139
00:10:52,670 --> 00:10:57,430
Then why did we find a note
with orders on it in your pocket?

140
00:10:57,430 --> 00:10:59,810
I thought I burned that letter!

141
00:10:59,810 --> 00:11:02,680
Oh! That was... well...

142
00:11:03,020 --> 00:11:07,610
Oh? But there wasn't
anything in your pocket.

143
00:11:14,150 --> 00:11:15,570
Princess Vivi...

144
00:11:15,570 --> 00:11:19,240
As I recall, that's the name
of the princess of Alabasta.

145
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:22,080
However, she's currently missing.

146
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:26,580
Alabasta's in the midst
of a coup, correct?

147
00:11:26,580 --> 00:11:32,210
Could this mysterious criminal organization
and the Straw Hats somehow be involved?

148
00:11:32,210 --> 00:11:33,710
Who knows?

149
00:11:33,710 --> 00:11:38,090
But this is the only clue leading us
to the Straw Hats right now.

150
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:40,680
So, we're going to...

151
00:11:41,260 --> 00:11:45,600
Yeah. Contact headquarters
and requisition an eternal pose!

152
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:46,140
Yes, sir!

153
00:11:48,100 --> 00:11:53,820
We're going to Alabasta,
the Kingdom of Sand!

154
00:11:53,860 --> 00:11:58,070
Little Garden, Island of Giants

155
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:11,170
We had completely forgotten
about the bounties on our heads!

156
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:16,130
If it weren't for me, they would have
never ventured to this island.

157
00:12:16,130 --> 00:12:16,800
Ow!

158
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:18,840
Enough of that.

159
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:22,470
Yeah, Vivi! What are you
so bummed about?

160
00:12:22,470 --> 00:12:23,470
Rice cracker?

161
00:12:23,470 --> 00:12:25,850
Wait, where'd those come from?

162
00:12:25,850 --> 00:12:28,810
All right! Time for a rice cracker party!

163
00:12:28,810 --> 00:12:31,110
Rice crackers aren't very exciting.

164
00:12:31,110 --> 00:12:32,820
So then, raise a toast with 'em.

165
00:12:32,820 --> 00:12:35,280
See? Does anyone blame you?

166
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:37,440
Cheers!

167
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:40,280
Look! What a waste! Honestly!

168
00:12:40,780 --> 00:12:43,950
Seriously, you'll just
ruin the food like that.

169
00:12:43,950 --> 00:12:47,290
What're you doing?! Give it here!
Who said you could have mine?!

170
00:12:47,290 --> 00:12:48,830
Give it back! It's mine!

171
00:12:48,830 --> 00:12:50,670
Says who?!

172
00:12:51,330 --> 00:12:52,210
What's wrong?

173
00:12:52,210 --> 00:12:54,170
Nothing. Just a bug.

174
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:59,050
Still, waiting a year for the log pose
to register the next island is no joke.

175
00:12:59,550 --> 00:13:02,510
You're right! It's no laughing matter!

176
00:13:03,050 --> 00:13:07,390
You saved us. We would like
to repay you in some way.

177
00:13:09,020 --> 00:13:12,350
Oh, in that case,
you old guys should fix our log!

178
00:13:13,690 --> 00:13:17,320
I'm afraid logs are the only thing
we can't help you with.

179
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:23,280
Nami my sweet! Vivi my love!
And the rest of you bums!

180
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:25,950
Hey! Sanji!

181
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:30,000
You're all safe! Thank goodness!

182
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:34,590
Of course that flake shows up
only after we need him.

183
00:13:37,090 --> 00:13:38,840
What the hell?!

184
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:41,090
Are you Mr. 3?!

185
00:13:41,430 --> 00:13:44,890
Hey! How do you know about Mr. 3?

186
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:46,600
Nami!

187
00:13:47,140 --> 00:13:49,220
What a risqué attire!

188
00:13:49,220 --> 00:13:50,350
Wanna risk my fist?

189
00:13:50,980 --> 00:13:52,980
Allow me, Nami.

190
00:13:52,980 --> 00:13:55,480
You'll catch a cold dressed like that.

191
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:56,860
Please, wear this.

192
00:13:56,860 --> 00:13:57,650
Thanks.

193
00:13:58,980 --> 00:14:03,610
All that aside, I just finished talking
with Mr. 0 via transponder snail.

194
00:14:04,370 --> 00:14:05,820
You talked to the boss?!

195
00:14:05,820 --> 00:14:10,540
Yeah. I found this weird hideout
in the jungle, you see.

196
00:14:10,910 --> 00:14:15,250
He seemed to think I was Mr. 3,

197
00:14:15,670 --> 00:14:19,090
so I told him I eliminated everyone.

198
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:22,550
So he thinks we're dead?!

199
00:14:22,930 --> 00:14:28,510
Even if we've shaken those chasing us,
we still can't go anywhere!

200
00:14:28,510 --> 00:14:30,140
Can't go anywhere?

201
00:14:30,140 --> 00:14:32,890
Do we still have business
on this island?

202
00:14:32,890 --> 00:14:35,810
I mean, I just got ahold of this, too.

203
00:14:43,070 --> 00:14:44,070
Uh? What?

204
00:14:44,530 --> 00:14:47,410
It's an eternal pose to Alabasta!

205
00:14:47,780 --> 00:14:49,540
– Hooray!
– Hooray!

206
00:14:49,540 --> 00:14:51,660
Now we can set sail!

207
00:14:51,660 --> 00:14:53,660
Hooray! Way to go, Sanji!

208
00:14:56,750 --> 00:14:58,460
Thank you, Sanji!

209
00:14:58,460 --> 00:15:00,170
I'd almost lost hope!

210
00:15:00,550 --> 00:15:03,550
No, no! It was my pleasure!

211
00:15:03,550 --> 00:15:05,630
I'm glad I could make you so happy!

212
00:15:06,050 --> 00:15:09,680
All right, everyone!
Let's have a rice cracker party!

213
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:11,970
Oh no, Luffy!

214
00:15:11,970 --> 00:15:14,270
It's not much of a party
with only three left!

215
00:15:14,270 --> 00:15:14,980
What?!

216
00:15:15,940 --> 00:15:18,690
All of that can be put on hold!

217
00:15:18,690 --> 00:15:19,820
Let's go, Captain!

218
00:15:19,820 --> 00:15:21,820
We can't waste a single second!

219
00:15:23,610 --> 00:15:24,950
Oh, yeah! Hey, you.

220
00:15:25,950 --> 00:15:28,910
You haven't forgotten
our hunting contest, I hope!

221
00:15:29,530 --> 00:15:32,040
Right! But I'm easily the winner.

222
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:34,120
I caught a rhino this big!

223
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:35,750
A rhino?

224
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:37,790
Is something like that edible?

225
00:15:37,790 --> 00:15:39,080
Of course!

226
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:41,040
A hunting contest?

227
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:43,050
A hunting contest?

228
00:15:43,050 --> 00:15:46,050
Those words sound familiar somehow.

229
00:15:46,050 --> 00:15:47,510
Mm-hmm.

230
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:52,470
All right, round old guy
and giant old guy!

231
00:15:52,470 --> 00:15:53,520
We're outta here!

232
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:59,400
Is that so? Well, you do
seem anxious to leave.

233
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,570
That's too bad,
but we won't stop you.

234
00:16:01,570 --> 00:16:03,530
Best of wishes for your country.

235
00:16:03,860 --> 00:16:05,530
Yes! Thank you!

236
00:16:05,860 --> 00:16:09,490
See ya! Don't die anymore!

237
00:16:09,950 --> 00:16:12,950
Master! I will visit Elbaph someday!

238
00:16:13,290 --> 00:16:16,080
You'll see. Mine's way
bigger than yours.

239
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:17,410
You wish!

240
00:16:19,040 --> 00:16:21,000
I'm gonna be
a brave warrior of the sea!

241
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:27,510
Our friends are setting sail.

242
00:16:27,510 --> 00:16:30,390
Yes. We can't just sit here.

243
00:16:30,390 --> 00:16:32,510
There's a monster in the western sea.

244
00:16:33,430 --> 00:16:35,930
Dorry, how are your wounds?

245
00:16:36,890 --> 00:16:38,940
These? I'll live.

246
00:16:42,730 --> 00:16:45,360
My axe and your sword
are just about finished.

247
00:16:48,740 --> 00:16:49,780
Second thoughts?

248
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:54,450
Of course. This axe has been my partner
in battle for well over a century.

249
00:16:54,450 --> 00:16:55,740
However,

250
00:16:55,740 --> 00:16:58,710
if it's to help them out,
then it's worth it!

251
00:16:59,210 --> 00:17:01,210
That settles it.

252
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:13,720
See?! Mine's much bigger than yours!

253
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:15,810
Look closer! My lizard's enormous!

254
00:17:16,390 --> 00:17:18,640
Are you blind or something?!

255
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:21,310
My rhino's much more humongous!

256
00:17:21,730 --> 00:17:23,900
Either way, they both look yummy!

257
00:17:24,230 --> 00:17:25,730
– Mind your own business!
– Mind your own business!

258
00:17:25,730 --> 00:17:26,230
Huh?

259
00:17:26,230 --> 00:17:30,530
– Look! Mine's bigger!
– No, mine is!

260
00:17:30,530 --> 00:17:32,660
How long do you two
plan to keep at it?

261
00:17:33,370 --> 00:17:38,120
Just butcher them and load what fits
so we can set sail!

262
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:39,620
Yes, Nami!

263
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:43,250
Hey, Usopp! I'm clearly
the winner, right?!

264
00:17:43,250 --> 00:17:45,130
Huh? I don't really care.

265
00:17:45,130 --> 00:17:46,630
Can't you call it a draw?

266
00:17:47,170 --> 00:17:49,010
There are no draws in a challenge!

267
00:17:49,010 --> 00:17:50,630
Move your asses!

268
00:17:51,680 --> 00:17:53,010
Right!

269
00:17:58,100 --> 00:18:00,430
Set sail!

270
00:18:04,770 --> 00:18:08,360
They said going straight will take us
to the western end of the island.

271
00:18:08,360 --> 00:18:11,110
Hey. Is this all the meat
we could carry?

272
00:18:11,110 --> 00:18:14,200
Use your head! We can't
preserve any more than this.

273
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:16,070
Do you want to sink the ship?!

274
00:18:22,460 --> 00:18:26,000
Look, it's the old guys!
They came to see us off!

275
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:33,930
Ahead is a great obstacle...

276
00:18:34,300 --> 00:18:38,890
...that prevents people who come
to this island from reaching the next.

277
00:18:41,060 --> 00:18:45,310
You fought desperately
to protect our pride.

278
00:18:45,310 --> 00:18:48,520
Therefore, no matter the enemy
that may rear its head...

279
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:55,070
...we will keep it from
trampling your pride, friends!

280
00:18:57,450 --> 00:18:59,910
Have faith and keep straight!

281
00:18:59,910 --> 00:19:02,750
No matter what happens,
sail straight ahead!

282
00:19:04,040 --> 00:19:05,370
Got it!

283
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:07,710
What's this about?

284
00:19:08,210 --> 00:19:09,670
Wh-What's the word?

285
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:12,630
We'll sail straight ahead,
no matter what happens!

286
00:19:20,260 --> 00:19:21,640
We bid you farewell!

287
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:23,390
Let us meet again someday.

288
00:19:23,390 --> 00:19:24,350
Without fail.

289
00:19:24,850 --> 00:19:25,730
Look! Ahead!

290
00:19:32,650 --> 00:19:34,190
There you are, Island Gorger!

291
00:19:34,700 --> 00:19:38,160
You will make way,
lest the pride of Elbaph fail us.

292
00:20:01,050 --> 00:20:01,930
Wha...?

293
00:20:01,930 --> 00:20:03,350
Something's appeared!

294
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:08,270
What is this guy? A goldfish?

295
00:20:09,100 --> 00:20:11,060
A g-giant goldfish?!

296
00:20:11,060 --> 00:20:13,230
Wh-Why does that sound familiar?!

297
00:20:13,230 --> 00:20:16,240
Work the rudder! Hurry!
We're gonna get eaten!

298
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:18,110
Usopp! Hurry!

299
00:20:18,110 --> 00:20:19,200
I... I can't!

300
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:22,080
Go straight ahead! R-Right, Luffy?!

301
00:20:23,490 --> 00:20:24,410
Of course!

302
00:20:30,750 --> 00:20:34,590
Don't be stupid! Laboon was one thing,
but this is nothing like him!

303
00:20:35,010 --> 00:20:37,720
I know. Don't worry.

304
00:20:37,720 --> 00:20:39,720
Here, have the last rice cracker.

305
00:20:40,050 --> 00:20:41,340
I don't want it!

306
00:20:41,340 --> 00:20:44,180
If we don't turn
the ship, we're gonna be...

307
00:20:46,060 --> 00:20:47,140
Just give it up, Nami.

308
00:20:52,020 --> 00:20:55,440
Luffy! We can trust
those guys, I take it?!

309
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:56,030
Yeah!

310
00:20:56,030 --> 00:20:59,490
Are you crazy?! Are we really
sailing straight into that beast?!

311
00:20:59,860 --> 00:21:02,450
Oh no! There's no turning back now!

312
00:21:11,460 --> 00:21:14,210
You've really grown, Island Gorger!

313
00:21:14,210 --> 00:21:15,880
You monstrous goldfish!

314
00:21:16,590 --> 00:21:19,840
His size isn't the only surprising thing.

315
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:22,760
This monster eats islands whole

316
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:25,760
and leaves behind
colossal lengths of dung.

317
00:21:25,760 --> 00:21:26,770
As I recall,

318
00:21:26,770 --> 00:21:29,730
one such floating dung heap
was named Nihiland.

319
00:21:32,350 --> 00:21:36,820
We actually landed on it long ago,
mistaking it for an island!

320
00:21:36,820 --> 00:21:39,320
Today makes me
nostalgic for adventure!

321
00:21:39,320 --> 00:21:42,280
As I watch that crew,
I'm reminded of the old days!

322
00:21:46,790 --> 00:21:51,460
The only thing we can't penetrate
is the bloodstained snake!

323
00:21:52,540 --> 00:21:56,710
Behold! The mighty, legendary spear
as taught only to those from Elbaph!

324
00:22:01,590 --> 00:22:03,550
Straight ahead! Straight ahead!

325
00:22:04,050 --> 00:22:06,810
What's the point?!
We've already been eaten!

326
00:22:07,180 --> 00:22:09,140
Straight ahead! Straight ahead!

327
00:22:17,570 --> 00:22:19,610
– Dominion!
– Dominion!

328
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:26,830
We're flying right out of it!

329
00:22:34,290 --> 00:22:37,420
Don't look back!
We're going straight ahead!

330
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:44,220
It's huge! So huge!

331
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:48,350
They cut... the very sea itself...

332
00:22:48,350 --> 00:22:52,180
This is the strength of Elbaph warriors!

333
00:22:53,230 --> 00:22:55,850
It's incredible!

334
00:23:08,330 --> 00:23:09,660
– Friends!
– Friends!

335
00:23:14,790 --> 00:23:16,880
– Now go!
– Now go!

336
00:23:27,430 --> 00:23:29,470
Long ago,

337
00:23:29,470 --> 00:23:33,770
there was a group of ruffians on the sea
known as the Giant Warrior Pirates.

338
00:23:34,180 --> 00:23:37,060
The two pirate chiefs,

339
00:23:37,060 --> 00:23:40,820
Brogy the Red Ogre
and Dorry the Blue Ogre,

340
00:23:40,820 --> 00:23:42,230
stood unrivaled in might.

341
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:47,200
Ordinary people no longer posed
a threat to them and steered clear.

342
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:53,080
But they say that the one
who finally put an end to their run...

343
00:23:53,620 --> 00:23:57,250
was a mere little girl.

344
00:24:00,250 --> 00:24:03,380
You see what
our chiefs caught today?!

345
00:24:03,380 --> 00:24:08,430
Yeah! It's all I can think about!
What a day to be alive!

346
00:24:08,430 --> 00:24:13,770
Each one of them bagged
an insanely huge sea king, after all!

347
00:24:14,270 --> 00:24:17,310
Even though we're Elbaph giants,

348
00:24:17,310 --> 00:24:22,610
nobody but the chiefs can take down
those jumbo-sized monsters!

349
00:24:22,610 --> 00:24:23,980
Right, men?!

350
00:24:24,730 --> 00:24:25,490
Yeah!

351
00:24:25,490 --> 00:24:27,280
You got that right!

352
00:24:30,370 --> 00:24:34,080
These ones are
definitely our biggest yet!

353
00:24:36,450 --> 00:24:39,000
Yeah! Bigger than anything
we've ever caught!

354
00:24:41,630 --> 00:24:43,800
So which one was bigger?

355
00:24:46,090 --> 00:24:46,920
Which...

356
00:24:46,920 --> 00:24:48,050
...one?

357
00:24:49,180 --> 00:24:51,220
Who won the hunting contest?

358
00:24:56,060 --> 00:24:59,890
Look, Brogy! Mine is slightly bigger!

359
00:24:59,890 --> 00:25:03,360
Keep dreaming! Mine's a whole
three centimeters longer!

360
00:25:03,360 --> 00:25:04,570
Say what?!

361
00:25:04,570 --> 00:25:05,610
What?!

362
00:25:05,610 --> 00:25:08,650
Chiefs! Please stop!

363
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:22,130
Incidentally, Brogy, there's one thing
I can't seem to remember.

364
00:25:22,130 --> 00:25:24,790
No, actually, that goes for me, too.

365
00:25:28,470 --> 00:25:29,760
The central mountain!

366
00:25:30,430 --> 00:25:31,760
No need to dwell on it!

367
00:25:31,760 --> 00:25:34,140
Let's settle this, once and for all!

368
00:25:34,550 --> 00:25:35,850
You're right!

369
00:25:35,850 --> 00:25:37,970
We'll sort things out afterward!
